Dear primaryFeather,

I'm working on a starling game and its almost done. The problem however is that I updated my starling version to the latest github version. What happened is the following:
- I updated starling
- Start my project and everything gets rendered
- Then, 1 frame after everything is rendered I get an error saying theres a null object reference in the function redrawContents in Textfield.as

I debugged this function and see following:

 if (mContents)
                if (mIsRenderedText) (mContents as Image).texture.dispose();   <-- this line
                mContents.removeFromParent(true);
 }

The error is created on that line, so I changed it to this:

 if (mContents)
            {
                if (mIsRenderedText){
                    var img:Image = mContents as Image;
                    img.texture.dispose();
                }
                mContents.removeFromParent(true);
            }

And then it turns out that img = null. In other words, it can not cast mContents to an Image.

Do you have any ideas about how this is possible? I never changed anything on the framework and just downloaded the latest version.

Cheers,
Marc from Holland
